OPENAI.name: OpenAI
OPENAI.tagline: AI research and deployment company developing artificial general intelligence to benefit humanity
OPENAI.overview: OpenAI is an AI research and deployment company founded in December 2015 by Sam Altman, Greg Brockman, Ilya Sutskever, Elon Musk, and others. Its mission is to ensure artificial general intelligence (AGI) benefits all of humanity. OpenAI started as a nonprofit research organization with $1 billion in pledged funding and transitioned to a capped-profit model in 2019 to attract additional investment. The company has developed groundbreaking AI systems including GPT-4o, ChatGPT, DALL-E, and Sora. As of October 2025, OpenAI has achieved a valuation of $500 billion following a secondary share sale, making it the world's most valuable private company. With over 800 million weekly active users and $13 billion in annualized revenue (up 3x YoY), OpenAI leads the global AI industry and is on track to reach $15-20B by year-end 2025.

OURA.name: Oura
OURA.tagline: Health technology company developing smart rings for sleep, activity, and wellness tracking
OURA.overview: Oura Health is a Finnish health technology company founded in 2013 by Petteri Lahtela, Kari Kivelä, and Markku Koskela. Known for its innovative smart ring that tracks biometric data including sleep, activity, heart rate, and body temperature, Oura has emerged as the leader in the smart ring market. As of September 2025, the company has achieved an $11 billion valuation following its $875 million Series E funding round. With over 5.5 million rings sold and revenue expected to exceed $1 billion in 2025, Oura continues to expand globally while advancing its AI-driven health insights and partnering with healthcare providers.

highlights.text: Acquired Sparta Science and Veri for expanded health capabilities.
Expanded to 4,000+ retail stores across 20 countries.
Reached 2 million paying subscribers for Oura Membership.
